<p><b>What is the just a minute jam topic?</b> Just A Minute (JAM) is a session where a candidate must speak on a given topic for one minute without hesitation or repetition. It tests communication skills, confidence, and ability to organize thoughts under pressure. Candidates should speak clearly and concisely on the topic, maintaining eye contact.</p>
<p><b>How to prepare for just a minute session?</b> Starting with a question or quotation will force them to listen to you. Questions are easy to prepare, but for the quotations, make sure you start learning the quotations from varied fields. Try adding your personal experience or some anecdotes in the speech − One minute or 60 seconds is a long enough time.</p>
<p><b>What is the just a minute format?</b> The object of the game is for panellists to talk for sixty seconds on a given subject, "without hesitation, repetition or deviation". The comedy comes from attempts to keep within these rules and the banter among the participants.</p>
