<p><b>What is the structure of just a minute session?</b> 'Just a Minute' (JAM) is basically a one minute or less extempore speech. It is an impromptu speech expected from the candidate. A group of 10 to 15 students are made to sit in a room and each student is given a topic. The HR expects the student to talk about the topic for a minute.</p>
